I have *very exciting* news! 

My third fabric collection has just been announced! Shops can begin preordering Moonchild now, and it’ll ship in September! ✨

I have been dying to share this collection with you all - it feels so completely me. Swipe through for a preview of the swatches and a preview of the patterns!

The collection includes two quilt patterns: Starly, a FQ friendly starry pattern with a fun secondary design in between blocks. And Reverie, a precut friendly, moon inspired pattern and the super extra exciting thing? WE ARE RELEASING AN ACRYLIC TEMPLATE! That works with Reverie, Memi’s Lemons, and Copihue!! 😱💃🏻🕺🏻🤩🥳

A little flashback Friday and St Paddy’s Day all wrapped in one! 

Green is probably my least used color… ever. But when my sister in law graduated college, a quilt in her favorite color was a must. I used my Whirlwind pattern for a fun modern quilt and dark green for the background fabric. It pushed me out of my comfort zone but I love, love how it turned out 😍💚

⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I was born and raised in Chile, but call Washington state home. I first learned to quilt while pregnant with my oldest in 2014. However, it wasn't until 2018 when I encountered the modern quilting movement that I was hooked.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Before starting Cotton and Joy I worked 8 years as a web designer and I originally created this space as a way to share my quilty adventures. However, the designer in me couldn't help to dream up my own designs and I soon learned how to draft quilt patterns.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I love designing quilts and contributing to the long tradition of quilting. My aim is to create a fast-finishes that anyone, from inexperienced beginners to long-time quilters, can enjoy making.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Be sure to follow #12minis12months3024 and #cosmicminiquilts to see what everyone is up to, meet the other designers and to sew along with us next year.

On my 5th Cotton and Joy anniversary in November of last last year, I took some time to reflect on my journey and realized I have released 26 quilt patterns so far! I am not the best at shining a light on my older patterns as I'm always focusing on releasing the next new pattern (RE: Annabelle Quilt comin' at ya Jan 12th 🤩). But this year, I wanted to make a change! So, I'm introducing Cotton and Joy Pattern of the Month! ⁣
⁣
Every month, we'll have a Pattern of the Month feature highlighting a pattern from the archive. Each Pattern of the Month will be on sale for that entire month, and we'll have new kits and notions available.⁣
⁣
We're starting the year off with Cabin Peaks as the January PotM! Inspired by Art Deco designs, this pattern uses the classic log cabin quilt block to create a modern design. This pattern is perfect for beginners ready to practice precision piecing and on point setting. ⁣
⁣
No code is needed to take advantage of the PotM sale! Cabin Peaks PDF and print patterns will be $9 (down from $13!) for the duration of the month of January and we have kits and new stickers available! 🥳⁣
